	painsBodyHtml={`<p>The mental load is the thread running through it all. Mothers carry roughly 71% of the household’s cognitive labor — the remembering, the planning, the noticing — an invisible weight that paid work and higher income never seem to lighten. Add the daily guilt, the comparison to curated lives online, and a body and mind worn thin by sleeplessness and self-forgetting, and many mothers arrive at a quiet, aching question: <em>who is mothering me?</em></p><p>These are not signs of a bad mother or a weak faith. They are the symptoms of a daughter who has been pouring out without being filled. There is a Father who sees every unseen thing you do — and who comforts you the way a mother comforts her child, before He ever asks anything of you.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
