	aFatherHeading={`A Father for mothers`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>The answer to a depleted mother is not a better system, more discipline, or one more thing to do for everyone else. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a holy Father for a beloved daughter who happens to be raising children, loving a family, mothering a world that rarely says thank you.</p><p>You spend your days mothering: feeding, comforting, remembering, holding everything together. But you cannot give a love you are not receiving. Long before you became anyone’s mother — biological, adoptive, step, foster, grand, or spiritual — you were a daughter of God. That is still the truest thing about you.</p><p>And here is the wonder of our God: He fathers you <em>and</em> He comforts you as a mother comforts her child (<a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/isaiah/66" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Isaiah 66:13</a>). So you wake tomorrow not first to serve, not first to perform — but to be loved by the One who never forgets you. You mother your family best from the overflow of being mothered by Him.</p>`}
