		{ ref: `Psalm 139:13`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 139, text: `For you formed my inmost being; you knit me together in my mother’s womb. I praise you, Father, for I am fearfully and wonderfully made.`, note: `The same Father who knit your children together knit you — you are His handiwork, not just a caretaker of His.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 127:3`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 127, text: `Children are a heritage from the Father, the fruit of the womb a reward from Him.`, note: `Your children are a gift from His hand, not a performance you must perfect — He entrusted them to you in love.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 40:11`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 40, text: `He tends his flock like a shepherd: he gathers the lambs in his arms and carries them close to his heart, and gently leads those that have young.`, note: `He gently leads the mothers — the ones nursing, the ones with little ones — carrying them close, not driving them hard.` },
