	offersBlocks={[
		{ heading: `Comfort the way you comfort`, bodyHtml: `To the one who soothes everyone else, the Father says <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/isaiah/66" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">“as a mother comforts her child, so will I comfort you.”</a> You are not only the comforter — you are the comforted.` },
		{ heading: `Rest for the weary`, bodyHtml: `To the mother running on empty, Jesus says <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/matthew/11" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">“come to me… and I will give you rest.”</a> You were never meant to be the endless source — only a daughter who drinks first.` },
		{ heading: `A Father who never forgets`, bodyHtml: `On the invisible days, He says <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/isaiah/49" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">“though a mother may forget, I will not forget you.”</a> Every unseen thing you do is seen and remembered by Him.` },
		{ heading: `A name beyond the role`, bodyHtml: `When the noise quiets, you are still His <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/139" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">fearfully and wonderfully made</a> daughter — your worth is your belovedness, not your productivity, your patience, or anyone’s approval.` },
