	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; George MacDonald, Andrew Murray, and Charles Spurgeon (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>When our Father said, “Let there be light,” there was light. His Word does what He sends it to do. Every prayer you whisper over a sleeping child, every truth you plant in a small heart, every unseen act of love — none of it comes back empty.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">“My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose.” <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What the Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>“Beloved daughter, before you ever held a child, I held you. I see every invisible thing — the lists you carry, the nights you don’t sleep, the love you give when no one is looking and no one says thank you. I see it all, and I treasure it.</p><p>Put down the guilt for a moment. You do not have to be everything to everyone — you only have to come to Me and be filled. Let Me comfort you the way you comfort your own; let Me carry you close, the way you carry your little ones. You are not just a mother to Me — you are My daughter, and I delight in you apart from anything you do. Be mothered by Me first. Then love your family from the overflow of being loved. I am your Father, and you are Mine.”</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for mothers`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for all mothers — biological, adoptive, step, foster, grand, and spiritual — the ones who carry the invisible load, who pour out endlessly, who hold whole families together while running on empty. Let them hear Your whisper above the noise of guilt and comparison and the relentless demands of the day. Let them encounter Your love — not as one more thing to do, but as a weight they feel — and experience Your delight over them, apart from how clean the house is or how patient they were today.</p><p>Give them grace to prioritize intimacy with You above their endless striving, and to receive their identity as Your daughters before they are anyone’s mother. Father, comfort them the way they comfort their own children; carry them close, the way they carry their little ones. Refill what has been poured out, and let them mother from the overflow of being mothered by You.</p><p>I pray Your protection over them from the enemy, from temptation, from the lie that they are failing, and from despair. Let them know there is no condemnation in You. Let them know You, their Father, as their true inheritance and reward, for every other gift pales beside the gift of You. And may they wake up every single day under the pour of their heavenly Father’s heart for them.</p><p>In Jesus’ name, amen.</p>`}
