	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for tired or overwhelmed mothers?`, answer: `Isaiah 66:13 (as a mother comforts her child, so I will comfort you), Matthew 11:28 (come to me and rest), Isaiah 49:15 (a mother may forget, yet I will not forget you), Isaiah 40:11 (he gently leads those with young), and Psalm 139 (fearfully and wonderfully made) all speak directly to a worn-out mom. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about mom guilt?`, answer: `Scripture answers mom guilt not with a higher standard but with belovedness. You are God's fearfully and wonderfully made daughter (Psalm 139), He never forgets you (Isaiah 49:15), and there is no condemnation for those in Christ. Your worth was never your performance. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you can read these passages free, with audio, and hear a Father who delights in you apart from how today went.` },
